i know bunnies eat salads but is it safe to put salad dressing on it i want to know but i don't want to expirement i don't want my bunny to get ill no you should not put dressing on it in fact a salad is not all that good for them iceberg lettuce does not have any nutritional value for a rabbit it is also high in water and can cause loose droppings you can give some veggies as a snack such as carrots they love apples for a treat actually dandelion greens and flowers are very good for rabbits they have potassium in them so basically like bunny bananas you can also add hay or alfalfa cubes to vary their diet many of the pet store rabbit feeds contain corn which is not good for rabbits and is more or less a filler there are many other more healthy alternatives to salad for your rabbit best of luck with your bunny Guinea pig Hamster Salad Rabbit Hamburger Potato McDonald's Cuisine of the Southern United States Alfalfa Fancy rat Salad Fingers Food Lettuce Potassium Sauerkraut Tofu Hypoglycemia Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography One Piece minor characters Cuisine of Denmark Escherichia coli O157:H7 Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Omega-3 fatty acid Nutrition Jewish cuisine Bread Kevin and Kell Easter Bunny Bugs Bunny Atkins Nutritional Approach Chinese New Year Healthy eating Sodium chloride Cat In-N-Out Burger Tomato Food preservation Japanese tea ceremony Egg (food) Taboo food and drink Trans fat Kiwifruit Peruvian cuisine Cuisine of Laos Apple Hay Carrot The Rabbit of Seville Dandelion Burdock Acorn Mango Goldfish Cuisine of Malaysia Organic farming German cuisine Sluggy Freelance Peanut Flowering plant Mel Blanc Banana Vegetarian cuisine Cuisine of Greece Cuisine of Singapore Tiny Toon Adventures Meal Bearded Dragon Chocolate Sauce Brandy and Mr. Whiskers Nutrient Pig (zodiac) Milk Sprouting The Care Bears Adventure in Wonderland Goatse.cx Vegetarianism Internet phenomenon Domesticated turkey Serbian cuisine Sandwich Shit Watermelon Care Be